            <Title>Step 5: Character Stories</Title>
            <Synopsis>Write a one-page description of each of the main characters and a half-page description for less important characters.

The purpose here is to tell the story from the point of view of that character. </Synopsis>
            <Notes>Take a day or two and write up a one-page description of each major character and a half-page description of the other important characters. These “character synopses” should tell the story from the point of view of each character. 
As always, feel free to cycle back to the earlier steps and make revisions as you learn cool stuff about your characters. I usually enjoy this step the most. I find it effective to put the resulting “character synopses” into my proposals in addition to a plot-based synopsis. 
Editors love character synopses, because editors love character-based fiction. 
If you’d like to see some examples of character synopses, look at the example Snowflakes included in Snowflake Pro. You can reach these from the File menu which has a submenu named Open Examples. </Notes>
