            <Title>Step 6: Expand Plot</Title>
            <Synopsis>Take your one-page plot synopsis and turn each paragraph from Step 4 into a whole page so that you end up with 4 pages in total.</Synopsis>
            <Notes>By now, you have a solid story and several story-threads, one for each character. 
Now take a week and expand the short synopsis of the novel to a long synopsis of about four pages. Basically, you will again be expanding each paragraph from Step 4 into a full page. This is a lot of fun, because you are figuring out the high-level logic of the story and making strategic decisions. 
Here, you will definitely want to cycle back and fix things in the earlier steps as you gain insight into the story and new ideas whack you in the face. 
If you’d like to see some examples of long synopses, look at the example Snowflakes included in Snowflake Pro. You can reach these from the File menu which has a submenu named Open Examples. I have a thorough discussion on writing synopses in chapter 9 of my book Writing Fiction for Dummies. </Notes>
        </Document>
